Introduction and Data Sheet Overview
The datasheet is that of Amazon sales for the years 2022 and 2023. The fields or columns that are part of this data set include 500 rows and 13 columns containing the following:
Order Id
Order Date
Product Type 
Pricing and Discount
Discounted Price
Total Revenue
The Quantity of Product Sold
The Customer’s Region
The Payment Method 
Rating and Review of the Product

Since Amazon is already a very popular E-Commerce brand, it is not surprising that the quantity and consumer willingness to purchase in this dataset is very high. The regions of purchase too are widely spread globally like Asia, Middle East, Europe and North America making their presence felt. 
The product range is also great and caters to a wide range of consumers. The products that are selling in a good scale according to the dataset include merchandise like fashion, home and kitchen products, beauty and skincare, books and stationery, sporting goods and electronics
The data set provides ample or required information to sort out the raw data and clean it after formatting and transforming it. Its also efficient to accordingly perform descriptive statistics and visualisations.

Sales, Revenue and Quantity in terms of Product Category
In terms of leading in revenue Home and Kitchen takes the lead followed by Electronics. The other categories of products like Books and Sports are considered middle sales and the other two Beauty and Fashion with Fashion being the least sold.
In terms of quantity or volume of products being sold Books are the most sold followed by Home and Kitchen. Electronics and Beauty are in the middle range followed by Sports and Fashion with Fashion being the least sold category. 

Sales, Revenue and Quantity in Terms of Customer Region
In terms of revenue generation across all categories and the total number of products sold, Asia takes the lead followed by Europe. Middle East is in the middle range while North America happens to be at the last position in terms of revenue generation.
In terms of Quantity Europe is at the lead position followed by Asia. Middle East remains at the middle position whereas North America comes down to the least.

Payment Methods in terms of Customer Region
Cash on Delivery – Europe is the highest followed by Asia and Middle East while North America is the least
Credit Card-Europe is the highest followed by Asia and Middle East and North America is the least once again
Debit Card- Europe is the highest followed by Asia and Middle East and North America is the least 
UPI- Asia is the highest followed by Europe and Middle East with North America being the least 
Wallet- Asia is the highest followed by Middle East and Europe and North America being the least once again

Payment Method in terms of Product Category
Wallet takes the lead in terms of payment method across product categories. This is followed by UPI, Cash on Delivery and Debit Card. Credit Card payment method is the least used method across all product categories.

Discount in terms of Product Category
Higher the discount higher the quantity sold meaning both of them are directly proportionate
Books have the highest discount sum so they are the most sold product.
Fashion has the least discount sum so it is the least sold product 
The rest of the products like Home and Kitchen, Electronics, Beauty, Sports also have discounts and even their quantity sold is proportional and in accordance with the discount that the particular category has received.

