Insights and Conclusion
Conclusion
a)	Pricing is sensible and with reasonable discount percentage and discounted price, the products are sold at a reasonable price.
b)	Revenue generated differs based on region of purchase and product category
c)	Higher discount leads to more quantity sold making it directly proportional 
d)	Consumer Behaviour analysis indicates strong customer loyalty presence in Europe followed by Asia and Middle East with North America being the least in consumer engagement
e)	Quantity sold also differs in each region and is directly proportional to both region and product category 
f)	When it comes to methods of payment, across product categories wallet payment is very popular and when it comes to region as well wallet is the most popular payment method.
Insights
a)	Customer engagement must be improved in North America
b)	Discounts help in revenue generation and improve consumer interest to purchase so wherever possible discounts must be provided 
c)	Whichever products are facing lower purchase rate across regions must be marketed better to improve the purchase rate in turn the revenue generation
d)	Consumer feedback must be more encouraged in order to observe customer pattern and curate business strategies accordingly
e)	Different payment methods must be promoted across product categories and regions to encourage diversity 
f)	In case of lower rate of profits, necessary measures to be taken in order to improve the profit rate by providing discounts and better marketing as mentioned earlier. 
